The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 28, 2009, as Family Day in the United States. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of families in shaping individuals' lives and highlights the challenges faced by families in the 21st century, such as balancing work and family life and protecting children from negative influences, including substance abuse. Obama urges parents to talk to their children about the risks of drug and alcohol use and encourages families to come together, foster open communication, and make healthy decisions. The proclamation calls upon the people of the United States to observe Family Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities to honor and strengthen the nation's families.